Gamma spectra were measured with the telescopic
scintillation pair spectrometer.
Recoil proton spectrometer was used for neutron

The energy resolution of gammas has been determined
by the energy width of the spectrometer response
function (1.65+-0.05MeV)and by the energy spread of the
neutron beam (1.35 MeV). The resulting resolutions are
14% at 15 MeV, and 10% at 21 MeV.
Absolute measurements
Natural or mono-isotopic compositions. Samples are
spheres and/or hemispheres of 4-6 cm diameter placed
close to the tritium target. Therefore the neutron
energy is spread over a range from 13.5 to 14.7 MeV.
Due to this geometry the spectra obtained are
integrated over a solid angle of 2(4) pi
